page.title: 02Places Of Interest.1.
page.content: {The Darnley Arms}is a medieval building.There are a number of old oak beams around the Darnley and also there is a tunnel leading from the cellar to the colleges round the back of the church.There is a good selection of wine,beer and fruit juices.The living quarters are upstairs where all of the floors are on a slant.{Owletts}is a large Georgion House built in 1684,situated at the end of the main street.It is a National Trust property,open to the public.Only two families have ever owned the property,the Hays and the Bakers.The three storeyed house has some fine fire places and an interesting collection of clocks. {The Leather Bottle }is an attractive inn with a mock tudor fascade and has strong connection with Charles Dickens ,being an inspiration for his novels.
